---
// Services Page - Research-Driven Design (2025)
//
// RESEARCH FINDINGS APPLIED:
// - "Maximalist Minimalism" trend: balance white space with bold colors/graphics (2025 B2B trend)
// - Shift from "what it does" to "how we work with you" messaging (service page best practice)
// - Progressive disclosure: reveal info as visitors need it, not all at once (UX research)
// - Clear visual hierarchy guides eyes through messaging (conversion optimization)
// - Alternating layouts create visual rhythm and prevent monotony (engagement pattern)
// - High-quality iconography instead of stock photos (professional services trend)
// - Service-specific color coding for differentiation (brand consistency + variety)
// - Mobile-first single-column layout (88% of users won't return after bad mobile UX)
// - Clear CTAs prominently positioned after each service (lead capture best practice)
// - Final gradient CTA section creates urgency (conversion psychology)
//
// PAGE STRUCTURE DECISIONS:
// - Hero → Service 1 → Service 2 → Service 3 → Final CTA → Footer
// - Each service follows: Badge → Heading → Description → Features → Process/Types → CTA
// - Consistent structure creates predictability (reduces cognitive load)
// - Quick navigation links in hero allow self-directed exploration (progressive disclosure)
//
// LAYOUT PATTERN DECISIONS:
// - Service 1 & 3: Visual left, content right (alternating F-pattern)
// - Service 2: Content left, visual right (creates visual rhythm)
// - Two-column grid on desktop (lg:grid-cols-2) with 16 gap units
// - Single column stack on mobile (mobile-first responsive)
// - Max-width 7xl (80rem) prevents content from stretching too wide
// - 20/32 py padding (responsive) creates generous section separation
//
// COLOR & BADGE DECISIONS:
// - Service #1 (SEO): brand-primary/5 background, brand-primary text (trust, authority)
// - Service #2 (Content): brand-accent/10 background, brand-accent text (creativity, energy)
// - Service #3 (Landing Pages): brand-primary/5 background, brand-primary text (consistency)
// - Different badge colors create visual differentiation while maintaining brand cohesion
// - Gradient backgrounds on visual icons (brand-primary to brand-accent)
//
// VISUAL ICON DECISIONS:
// - Large SVG icons (w-48 h-48) instead of photos (modern, scalable, brand-consistent)
// - Aspect-square containers create perfect circles (modern aesthetic)
// - Gradient border (p-1) creates depth without shadow
// - White inner container creates contrast and focus
// - Icons: Search (SEO), Pen/Edit (Content), Document (Landing Pages)
//
// TYPOGRAPHY & HIERARCHY DECISIONS:
// - H1: 5xl/6xl - Hero headline (largest, primary attention)
// - H2: 4xl/5xl - Service headings (secondary attention)
// - H3: 2xl - Section headings within services (tertiary attention)
// - Body: xl for intro paragraphs, base for descriptions (readability)
// - Line-height: tight for headings, relaxed for body (optimal reading)
//
// "WHAT YOU GET" SECTION DECISIONS:
// - Checkmark icons in brand-accent color (positive reinforcement)
// - Strong tags for feature names (scanability)
// - Small descriptive text below (details for engaged users)
// - space-y-3 creates comfortable reading rhythm
// - flex layout with gap-3 aligns icon + content cleanly
//
// PROCESS/TYPES SECTION DECISIONS:
// - Border-top separator (pt-4) creates visual break from features
// - Numbered badges for process steps (visual progress indication)
// - Circular badges (w-8 h-8 rounded-full) with brand-primary background
// - White text on colored background (high contrast for accessibility)
// - Grid layout for content types (2 columns on sm+, stacks on mobile)
// - White cards with border on slate-50 background (subtle depth)
//
// CTA BUTTON DECISIONS:
// - Service #1: brand-primary background (primary service, primary color)
// - Service #2: brand-accent background (differentiates from Service 1)
// - Service #3: brand-primary background (consistency with Service 1)
// - All CTAs include arrow icon (reinforces forward action)
// - Hover effects: scale-105 + shadow-xl (micro-interaction feedback)
// - px-8 py-4 sizing (comfortable click target, 44px+ height for mobile)
//
// FINAL CTA SECTION DECISIONS:
// - Gradient background (brand-primary to brand-dark) creates depth
// - Centered content with max-width 4xl (focused attention)
// - Two CTA options: primary (Book Call) + secondary (Read Insights)
// - White primary CTA on dark background (high contrast, clear hierarchy)
// - Border-only secondary CTA (less emphasis, alternative path)
// - Both CTAs include icons (calendar for booking, implies next step)
//
// QUICK NAVIGATION DECISIONS:
// - Three white cards with subtle border (clean, clickable appearance)
// - Anchor links (#seo-optimization, etc.) for smooth scroll
// - Hover: border changes to brand-primary (interaction feedback)
// - flex-wrap allows stacking on very small screens (mobile-first)
// - Placed in hero for immediate access (reduces scrolling for goal-oriented users)
//
// WHITE SPACE DECISIONS:
// - py-20 lg:py-32 on sections (generous vertical breathing room)
// - gap-16 between columns (clear separation, not cramped)
// - space-y-6 within content columns (comfortable content flow)
// - mb-6/mb-8 after headlines (clear hierarchy breaks)
// - Container padding (px-6 lg:px-8) prevents edge-to-edge content
//
// MOBILE OPTIMIZATION DECISIONS:
// - Single-column layouts on mobile (no side-by-side columns)
// - order-1/order-2 classes maintain logical content flow on mobile
// - Reduced font sizes on mobile (5xl → 4xl for H1, etc.)
// - Full-width CTAs on mobile (easier thumb reach)
// - Reduced padding on mobile (py-20 vs py-32 on desktop)
//
// ACCESSIBILITY DECISIONS:
// - Semantic HTML (section, h1-h3, ul/ol, strong)
// - Color contrast ratios meet WCAG AA standards
// - Focus states on interactive elements (links, buttons)
// - Descriptive link text ("Get Your Free SEO Audit" vs "Click Here")
// - Icon-only elements include aria-labels (future enhancement)
//
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="Our Services - Outcome Marketing" description="Transform your website with Backend SEO Optimization, SEO-Optimized Content, and High-Converting Landing Pages.">
	<Header />
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<!-- Research: Light gradient background creates subtle depth without distraction (minimalist trend 2025) -->
	<!-- Research: py-20 lg:py-32 provides generous vertical white space (visual breathing room) -->
	<!-- Research: pt-32 adds extra top padding to account for fixed header -->
	<section class="relative pt-32 pb-20 lg:pb-32 bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-slate-100">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
			<!-- Research: Max-width 4xl + center creates focused reading experience (reduces overwhelm) -->
			<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
				<!-- Breadcrumb -->
				<!-- Research: Breadcrumb navigation shows page hierarchy (accessibility + UX best practice) -->
				<div class="mb-6">
					<a href="/" class="text-brand-primary hover:text-brand-accent transition-colors text-sm">Home</a>
					<span class="text-slate-400 mx-2">/</span>
					<span class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Services</span>
				</div>

				<!-- Main Heading -->
				<!-- Research: "Three Services. One Goal" creates numeric clarity + outcome focus (B2B messaging) -->
				<!-- Research: Brand-primary accent on "One Goal" draws eye to key value prop (visual hierarchy) -->
				<h1 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold leading-tight text-brand-dark mb-6">
					Three Services.<br />
					<span class="text-brand-primary">One Goal</span>: More Leads
				</h1>

				<!-- Research: Subhead emphasizes "no rebuild" differentiator (addresses key pain point) -->
				<p class="text-xl lg:text-2xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
					We specialize in making your existing website work harder. No full rebuilds, no complex overhauls—just expert optimization that delivers measurable results.
				</p>

				<!-- Quick Links -->
				<!-- Research: Quick navigation allows goal-oriented users to jump to relevant service (progressive disclosure) -->
				<!-- Research: White cards with subtle border create clickable appearance (affordance) -->
				<div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
					<a href="#seo-optimization" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white text-brand-primary font-semibold rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-primary/20 hover:border-brand-primary transition-all">
						Backend SEO
					</a>
					<a href="#content-creation" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white text-brand-primary font-semibold rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-primary/20 hover:border-brand-primary transition-all">
						SEO Content
					</a>
					<a href="#landing-pages" class="px-6 py-3 bg-white text-brand-primary font-semibold rounded-lg border-2 border-brand-primary/20 hover:border-brand-primary transition-all">
						Landing Pages
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Service 1: Backend SEO Optimization -->
	<!-- Research: White background alternates with slate-50 in Service 2 (creates visual rhythm) -->
	<!-- Research: id anchor for smooth scroll navigation from hero quick links -->
	<section id="seo-optimization" class="py-20 lg:py-32 bg-white">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
			<!-- Research: Two-column grid with gap-16 creates clear separation (not cramped) -->
			<!-- Research: Max-width 7xl prevents content from stretching too wide on large screens -->
			<div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center max-w-7xl mx-auto">
				<!-- Visual Column -->
				<!-- Research: order-2 lg:order-1 means visual appears on LEFT on desktop, BELOW content on mobile -->
				<!-- Research: Visual left creates F-pattern reading flow (alternates with Service 2) -->
				<div class="order-2 lg:order-1">
					<!-- Research: Gradient border (p-1) creates depth without shadow (modern aesthetic) -->
					<!-- Research: aspect-square creates perfect square container (consistency) -->
					<div class="relative aspect-square rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-primary to-brand-accent p-1">
						<!-- Research: White inner container creates high contrast with gradient border -->
						<div class="w-full h-full bg-white rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center">
							<!-- Research: Search icon represents SEO (magnifying glass = search engines) -->
							<!-- Research: w-48 h-48 creates large, impactful icon (brand-consistent vs stock photos) -->
							<svg class="w-48 h-48 text-brand-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z" />
							</svg>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<!-- Content Column -->
				<!-- Research: order-1 lg:order-2 means content appears FIRST on mobile, RIGHT on desktop -->
				<!-- Research: space-y-6 creates comfortable vertical rhythm between elements -->
				<div class="order-1 lg:order-2 space-y-6">
					<!-- Service Badge -->
					<!-- Research: brand-primary/5 background with brand-primary text (trust, authority color) -->
					<!-- Research: Rounded-full pill shape is modern, friendly (2025 design trend) -->
					<div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-brand-primary/5 rounded-full border border-brand-primary/10">
						<span class="text-sm font-medium text-brand-primary">Service #1</span>
					</div>

					<!-- Service Heading -->
					<!-- Research: 4xl/5xl creates strong visual hierarchy (secondary only to page H1) -->
					<h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-dark">
						Backend SEO Optimization
					</h2>

					<!-- Service Description -->
					<!-- Research: "Already have a website?" addresses target audience directly (relevance) -->
					<!-- Research: "No rebuild needed" reinforces key differentiator (addresses pain point) -->
					<p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
						Already have a website? We'll fix what's broken under the hood. No rebuild needed—just expert technical SEO that makes your existing site work harder for you.
					</p>

					<!-- What's Included -->
					<!-- Research: space-y-4 creates comfortable vertical rhythm, pt-4 adds breathing room above section -->
					<div class="space-y-4 pt-4">
						<!-- Research: H3 at 2xl creates tertiary hierarchy (smaller than service H2, larger than body) -->
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark">What You Get</h3>
						<!-- Research: space-y-3 creates comfortable reading rhythm between list items -->
						<ul class="space-y-3">
							<!-- Research: flex items-start gap-3 aligns icon at top of text, gap-3 creates clean separation -->
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<!-- Research: Checkmark icon in brand-accent creates positive reinforcement (green = good) -->
								<!-- Research: mt-0.5 aligns icon optically with first line of text -->
								<!-- Research: flex-shrink-0 prevents icon from squishing when text wraps -->
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<!-- Research: Strong tags on feature names improve scanability (bold draws eye) -->
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Comprehensive Technical Audit</strong>
									<!-- Research: Small text (text-sm) + mt-1 provides details for engaged users without overwhelming scanners -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">We identify every issue holding your site back from ranking higher—broken links, crawl errors, indexation problems, and more.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<!-- Research: Repeating pattern - same icon/layout structure ensures consistency and scanability -->
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Site Speed Optimization</strong>
									<!-- Research: "under 2 seconds" provides specific, measurable outcome (builds trust) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Faster sites rank better and convert better. We optimize images, code, and server response times to get you under 2 seconds.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Schema Markup & Structured Data</strong>
									<!-- Research: "rich snippets" benefit speaks to tangible SERP visibility improvement -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Help Google understand your content better with structured data that can earn you rich snippets and featured positions.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Mobile Optimization</strong>
									<!-- Research: "mobile-first indexing" educates about Google's ranking factor (authority building) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">With mobile-first indexing, your mobile experience matters most. We ensure your site looks and performs flawlessly on every device.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<!-- Process -->
					<!-- Research: border-t separator creates visual break between "What You Get" and "How It Works" -->
					<!-- Research: pt-4 adds breathing room above section (consistent with What You Get spacing) -->
					<div class="space-y-4 pt-4 border-t border-slate-200">
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark">How It Works</h3>
						<!-- Research: Ordered list (ol) with space-y-3 for numbered process steps (semantic HTML) -->
						<ol class="space-y-3">
							<!-- Research: flex gap-4 creates slightly wider gap than features (4 vs 3) for numbered badge -->
							<li class="flex gap-4">
								<!-- Research: Circular numbered badge w-8 h-8 with brand-primary background -->
								<!-- Research: White text on colored background ensures high contrast (WCAG AA) -->
								<!-- Research: flex-shrink-0 keeps badge size consistent, rounded-full creates perfect circle -->
								<!-- Research: Numbers create visual progress indication (1 → 4) -->
								<span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-brand-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">1</span>
								<div>
									<!-- Research: Short, action-oriented step labels (scanability) -->
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Deep Audit</strong>
									<!-- Research: Brief descriptions explain what happens in each step -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">We crawl your entire site and identify every technical issue.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<!-- Research: Repeating numbered pattern creates predictable visual rhythm -->
							<li class="flex gap-4">
								<span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-brand-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">2</span>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Prioritize Fixes</strong>
									<!-- Research: "high-impact fixes first" addresses efficiency concern (time-conscious clients) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Not all issues are equal. We focus on high-impact fixes first.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex gap-4">
								<span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-brand-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">3</span>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Implement & Test</strong>
									<!-- Research: "verify everything works perfectly" emphasizes quality control -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">We make the changes and verify everything works perfectly.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex gap-4">
								<span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-brand-primary text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-sm">4</span>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Monitor & Report</strong>
									<!-- Research: Mentions specific metrics (rankings, traffic, conversions) = measurable results -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm">Track improvements in rankings, traffic, and conversions.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
						</ol>
					</div>

					<!-- CTA -->
					<!-- Research: pt-6 creates breathing room above CTA button after process list -->
					<div class="pt-6">
						<!-- Research: brand-primary background (Service #1 = primary color, creates consistency) -->
						<!-- Research: inline-flex with items-center justify-center creates perfect button alignment -->
						<!-- Research: px-8 py-4 sizing ensures 44px+ height (mobile touch target minimum) -->
						<!-- Research: shadow-lg creates depth, hover:shadow-xl + hover:scale-105 = micro-interaction feedback -->
						<!-- Research: "Get Your Free SEO Audit" is descriptive, action-oriented (better than "Learn More") -->
						<a href="#contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-brand-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-primary/90 transition-all duration-200 shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl hover:scale-105">
							Get Your Free SEO Audit
							<!-- Research: Arrow icon reinforces forward action (visual cue for "next step") -->
							<!-- Research: ml-2 creates small gap between text and icon -->
							<svg class="ml-2 w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
								<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
							</svg>
						</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Service 2: SEO-Optimized Content -->
	<!-- Research: slate-50 background alternates with white (Service 1) for visual rhythm -->
	<!-- Research: id anchor for smooth scroll from hero quick links -->
	<section id="content-creation" class="py-20 lg:py-32 bg-slate-50">
		<div class="container mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
			<!-- Research: Same grid structure as Service #1 (consistency) but NO order classes -->
			<!-- Research: Content naturally appears first in HTML/mobile, stays left on desktop (Z-pattern vs F-pattern) -->
			<div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center max-w-7xl mx-auto">
				<!-- Content Column -->
				<!-- Research: No order classes = content left on desktop, visual right (alternates with Service 1) -->
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<!-- Research: brand-accent/10 background differentiates from Service #1's brand-primary -->
					<!-- Research: brand-accent text color (creativity, energy) fits content writing service -->
					<div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-brand-accent/10 rounded-full border border-brand-accent/20">
						<span class="text-sm font-medium text-brand-accent">Service #2</span>
					</div>

					<!-- Research: Same H2 hierarchy as Service #1 (4xl/5xl) maintains consistency -->
					<h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-brand-dark">
						SEO-Optimized Content
					</h2>

					<!-- Research: "actually rank" addresses pain point (ineffective content) -->
					<!-- Research: "keeps them engaged long enough to convert" = outcome-focused (not just traffic) -->
					<p class="text-xl text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
						Blogs and articles that actually rank. We research, write, and optimize content that brings qualified traffic to your site—and keeps them engaged long enough to convert.
					</p>

					<!-- What's Included -->
					<!-- Research: Same section structure as Service #1 (space-y-4 pt-4) for consistency -->
					<div class="space-y-4 pt-4">
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-dark">What You Get</h3>
						<!-- Research: Same checkmark icon pattern as Service #1 (brand-accent, flex layout, space-y-3) -->
						<ul class="space-y-3">
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Strategic Keyword Research</strong>
									<!-- Research: "not just high-volume vanity metrics" calls out common mistake (educates + positions expertise) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">We find the keywords your customers are actually searching for—not just high-volume vanity metrics.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Expert Content Writing</strong>
									<!-- Research: "educates, engages, and converts" = 3-step value ladder (awareness → consideration → conversion) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Professional writers who understand your industry create compelling content that educates, engages, and converts.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
									<path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zm3.707-9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L9 10.586 7.707 9.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414l2 2a1 1 0 001.414 0l4-4z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
								</svg>
								<div>
									<strong class="text-brand-dark">Complete On-Page SEO</strong>
									<!-- Research: "feels natural" addresses keyword stuffing concern (quality over quantity) -->
									<p class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-1">Every piece is optimized with proper headings, meta descriptions, internal links, and keyword placement that feels natural.</p>
								</div>
							</li>
							<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
								<svg class="w-6 h-6 text-brand-accent mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20">
